<subSubSection id="C368652E93558E08F2AAFB7CFB00FAE7" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593558E08F2AAFB7CFB00FAE7" blockId="12.[151,1437,1262,1540]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF893558E08F2AAFB7CFB1CFAE7" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147305" collectorName="J. Serrano" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="lectotype">
The specimen here designated as 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793558E08F021FB7CFD52FAC3" box="[540,643,1262,1288]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">lectotype</typeStatus>
is a male bearing labels “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693558E08F18EFB7CFBCCFAC3" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[947,1053,1262,1288]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsoletus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793558E08F18EFB7CFBCCFAC3" box="[947,1053,1262,1288]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">obsoletus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
m. in Gallia merid.”, “ex-Museo Chaudoir” and “ 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793558E08F371FA80FE6EFAE7" box="[332,447,1298,1324]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">Lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693558E08F3D9FA80FC0BFAE7" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[484,986,1298,1324]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsoletus" subGenus="Ophonus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793558E08F3D9FA80FCECFAE7" box="[484,829,1298,1324]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">Harpalus (Ophonus) obsoletus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493558E08F179FA80FC0BFAE7" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[836,986,1298,1324]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
desig. by 
<collectorName id="2687537393558E08F670FA80FB12FAE7" box="[1101,1219,1298,1324]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">J. Serrano</collectorName>
”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E93558E08F2FAFAA4FB85F9CF" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593558E08F2FAFAA4FE7AFA2B" blockId="12.[151,1437,1262,1540]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">
The 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793558E08F2C7FAA4FEB0FA9B" box="[250,353,1334,1360]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">lectotype</typeStatus>
shows a transverse pronotum slightly cordiform, with posterior angles of pronotum well marked but not protruding backwards, and the prosternum slightly punctured. These characters allow to distinguish this species from 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693558E08F335FAEDFE55FA53" box="[264,388,1406,1432]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Ophonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793558E08F335FAEDFE55FA53" box="[264,388,1406,1432]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">D. pallidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In both species the dark spot of elytra is variable, from clearly marked to almost erased; this colour variation is perhaps related to life in salty places. For keys to the species see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493558E08F674FA30FB3BFA77" author="Fuente de la, J. M." box="[1097,1258,1442,1468]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" refId="ref10490" refString="Fuente de la, J. M. (1927) Tablas analiticas para la clasificacion de los coleopteros de la Peninsula Iberica. Adephaga: I Cicindelidae, II Carabidae. J. Bosch, Barcelona, 415 pp." type="book" year="1927">Fuente (1927)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493558E08F6CBFA30FA4DFA77" author="Jeannel, R." box="[1270,1436,1442,1468]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" pagination="572 - 1173" refId="ref11231" refString="Jeannel, R. (1942) Coleopteres carabiques. Deuxieme partie. Faune de France 40. Librairie de la Faculte des Sciences, Paris, pp. 572 - 1173." type="book chapter" year="1942">Jeannel (1942)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493558E08F2FBFA54FE86FA2B" author="Wrase, D. W." box="[198,343,1478,1504]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" pagination="344 - 386" refId="ref12516" refString="Wrase, D. W. (2004) Harpalina. In: Freude, H., Harde, K. W., Lohse, G. A. &amp; Klausnitzer, B. (Eds.), Die Kafer Mitteleuropas. Bd. 2 Adephaga 1: Carabidae (Laufkafer). Spektrum-Verlag, Heidelberg / Berlin, pp. 344 - 386." type="book chapter" year="2004">Wrase (2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493558E08F35EFA54FE4EFA2B" author="Wrase, D. W." box="[355,415,1478,1504]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" refId="ref12634" refString="Wrase, D. W. (2011) Genus Tschitscherinellus. Arndt, E., Schnitter, P., Sfenthourakis, S. &amp; Wrase, D. W. (Eds.), Ground beetles (Carabidae) of Greece. Pensoft, Sofia, pp. 163." type="book" year="2011">2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593558E08F2FAFA78FB85F9CF" blockId="12.[151,1437,1262,1540]" box="[199,1108,1514,1540]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">It is recorded in Central and Mediterranean Europe, North Africa and the Levant.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
